<HL>
   International Brief -- Roche Holding AG:
   First-Half Sales Rose 6%;
   Higher 1990 Net Expected
</HL>
<DATE>
07/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   Z.HR
</CO>
<LP>
   Roche Holding AG, parent of a Swiss drug and chemical
group, said in Basel that its first-half group sales rose 6%
to 5.18 billion francs ($3.65 billion) from 4.89 billion
francs a year earlier.
   The company also said that it expects to post a higher
profit this year, although in this regard it also mentioned
exchange rate uncertainties.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Profit in 1989 rose 33% to 852 million francs on a 21%
increase in group sales to 9.81 billion francs.
</TEXT>
